init_text:
Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

actions.text: Listening to books can be a great way to work through reading tasks and gain a new perspective on what one has read.

actions.text: It may not be possible to truly immerse oneself in a book when listening instead of reading.
